<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1618007-hi-all-great-story-but-one-consistent">Hi All,
GREAT story, but one consistent (annoying) grammatical error overlooked by author and obviously-every editor on the team;
 Each time Pears writes the word &quot;HISTORICAL&quot; preceded by an article, he uses &quot;AN.&quot;
&quot;An historical&quot;...event, etc. is wrong.
To confirm this, I checked out:.https://www.dailywritingtips.com/a-historic-vs-an-historic/.
Arguments?</a>
</div>
