        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2758549655" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9841055163460105814">The year was 1663. An English king had freshly mounted the throne; civil war hardly a memory behind him. Political intrigue and religious strife swept across the land, sending a rogue but heady breeze through the university town of Oxford. Four men are called upon to recollect the events of those days - a gentleman of Venice, a student, a cryptographer and an archivist. Each account builds upon the one that went before, challenging the truth and ever-complicating the circumstances surrounding th</span>
  <span id="freeText9841055163460105814" style="display:none">The year was 1663. An English king had freshly mounted the throne; civil war hardly a memory behind him. Political intrigue and religious strife swept across the land, sending a rogue but heady breeze through the university town of Oxford. Four men are called upon to recollect the events of those days - a gentleman of Venice, a student, a cryptographer and an archivist. Each account builds upon the one that went before, challenging the truth and ever-complicating the circumstances surrounding the death of a low-born woman with a treasonous past.<br /><br />This is a thick book designed for a comfortable chair and about a week's worth of inclement weather. Should you find yourself graced with such a turn of luck, here is a story to fit the fortune...filled with intellectual attractions and not a single literary regret.<br /></span>
