<div id="review_15504604" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/15504604" />
    <a title="Jamie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/887262-jamie"><img alt="Jamie" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/15504604?book_show_action=true">Feb 15, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jamie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jamie" href="/user/show/887262-jamie">Jamie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">anyone who wants to see how good fiction can be.</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer15504604" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6433009899190321844">This is still the gold standard of all historical fiction for me. I&apos;ve tried to find its equal and haven&apos;t come up with it. The four contemporary accountings of the same events, the disagreement between the various witnesses, the lofty intellectual language, the extensive historical accuracy of the period and location... this is just what great historical fiction is supposed to be. I&apos;ve read several of this author&apos;s other works now and they&apos;re all good, but this is simply that much better. Fasci</span>
  <span id="freeText6433009899190321844" style="display:none">This is still the gold standard of all historical fiction for me. I've tried to find its equal and haven't come up with it. The four contemporary accountings of the same events, the disagreement between the various witnesses, the lofty intellectual language, the extensive historical accuracy of the period and location... this is just what great historical fiction is supposed to be. I've read several of this author's other works now and they're all good, but this is simply that much better. Fascinating period, great characters, and a very clever, engrossing story told through the various people who were witness to it. A great recipe that few authors have the talent to follow.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6433009899190321844" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


